body: Thank  you for your reply. I think controller.cc and controller.h are the main roadblock for Linux.  I will check out onnx's tutorials.  I hope people at Microsoft will be interested in porting the sample to Linux.

Hi @jinz2014, the sample depends on Windows Thread Pool API, which is part of Windows Kernel. So it is not available on Linux. 

I suggest you may create a simplified sample reader. Basically, you should have a thread pool, which read and decode image files in multiple threads, and put the results in a queue. The sample reader is the producer of the queue, you should have another thread pool that consumes the queue and invoke ORT functions to run the inference.
Hi @snnn, the imagenet example provides posix source code for synchronization and file system. What was the purpose of the posix API, is it still maintained?
